  "text": "In this manner, we assigned 11 BAC clones to eight different alpaca autosomes. Most of the candidate genes were mapped to a specific G-band or a range of G-bands ( Table 2) . Previously mapped reference markers [CITATION_1] confirmed chromosome identification and helped to position new genes in the centromere-telomere field (Figure 1) . Four genes were TABLE 2 | Summary data of newly mapped genes and reference markers [CITATION_2] VicPac2.0.2 scaffolds in bold denote those that were chromosomally assigned first time in this study.",
